data.content:
## .NET 10 OpenAPI Breaking Changes

The root cause is that `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` 10.0 upgraded from **OpenAPI.NET v1** to **OpenAPI.NET v2**, which has several breaking changes affecting your code:

### 1. `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace removed
All `OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, `OpenApiBoolean`, etc. types are gone. Use `System.Text.Json.Nodes` instead.

```csharp
// ❌ Before
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// ✅ After
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

### 2. `Schema.Nullable` property removed
OpenAPI.NET v2 targets OpenAPI 3.1, where `nullable` is no longer a keyword. Instead, null is expressed as a type flag via the `JsonSchemaType` flags enum.

```csharp
// ❌ Before
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// ✅ After — clear the Null flag from the Type
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

You'll need `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;` (already present) for `JsonSchemaType`.

### 3. Everything else stays the same
`OpenApiResponse`, `OpenApiSecurityScheme`, `OpenApiReference`, `ReferenceType`, and `OpenApiSecurityRequirement` are unchanged in shape for your usage.

---

### Fixed code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;        // replaces Microsoft.OpenApi.Any
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");  // was OpenApiString
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
    {
        Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
    };
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;  // was Nullable = false
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

### Summary of changes

| What changed | v1 (`.NET 9`) | v2 (`.NET 10`) |
|---|---|---|
| Example values | `new OpenApiString("1.0")` | `JsonValue.Create("1.0")` |
| Namespace | `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` | `System.Text.Json.Nodes` |
| Nullable control | `schema.Nullable = bool` | `schema.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` |
